01:23.198 --> 01:24.499
I hate surprises.

01:24.566 --> 01:26.000
Yeah?
Yes.

01:26.067 --> 01:28.002
You didn't mind when I surprised
you with my promotion.

01:28.069 --> 01:30.710
Well, that wasn't a surprise, that
was earned by my genius husband.

01:30.773 --> 01:32.056
Good answer by my genius wife.

01:32.123 --> 01:34.058
See, I thought you only
liked me for my body.

01:34.126 --> 01:36.361
I do like you for your body.

01:36.429 --> 01:38.129
What are we doing?

01:40.166 --> 01:41.449
Surprise.

01:44.537 --> 01:46.821
I don't understand.
What is it?

01:46.888 --> 01:48.923
It's a house.
Yes.

01:48.991 --> 01:51.859
Yes, I can see that.
Thank you.

01:51.927 --> 01:55.213
Also known as a home,
sanctuary, dwelling.

01:55.280 --> 01:57.448
Yeah?

01:57.516 --> 02:00.118
Or, if you like,
you could just call it ours.

02:01.453 --> 02:03.404
Ours?
Mmm-hmm.

02:04.856 --> 02:05.907
Where would we get the money?

02:05.975 --> 02:08.743
I mean, how do we get
into something like this?

02:08.811 --> 02:10.443
Oh, I don't know.

02:12.547 --> 02:14.515
Maybe with a key.

02:17.820 --> 02:20.855
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God, are you kidding?

02:24.927 --> 02:26.728
It's a classic.

02:26.795 --> 02:28.713
1920s, wood-frame.

02:28.780 --> 02:30.865
Three bedroom,
one-and-a-half bath.

02:30.933 --> 02:33.818
And the old owners even left us
a brand-new swing set out back.

02:33.886 --> 02:36.371
Oh, well, I think I'm a
little big for swing sets.

02:36.438 --> 02:39.374
We have to fill up those spare
rooms sometime soon, right?

02:39.441 --> 02:40.841
Thank you.

02:48.734 --> 02:51.419
I love you.
I love you, too.

02:51.487 --> 02:52.987
Let's go home.

03:15.377 --> 03:16.544
Mommy?

03:18.597 --> 03:20.181
Mommy?
Hmm.

03:20.248 --> 03:22.383
When's Daddy coming home?

03:22.451 --> 03:23.617
What, baby?

03:23.685 --> 03:25.686
When's Daddy coming home?

03:25.754 --> 03:26.754
Um...

03:28.891 --> 03:31.792
Today, baby. It was just
an overnight trip.

03:32.694 --> 03:34.295
Why couldn't he take us?

03:34.363 --> 03:36.965
Because it was work
and we couldn't go.

03:37.032 --> 03:39.049
But how about a,
"Good morning, Mommy.

03:39.117 --> 03:40.768
"Nice to see you."
Good morning, Mommy.

03:40.903 --> 03:42.470
Mom, you gotta get dressed.

03:42.621 --> 03:45.690
Sweetie, we got plenty of time.

03:45.758 --> 03:48.443
We're gonna be late for school.
Oh, no.

03:48.510 --> 03:50.961
We're not gonna be
late for school.

03:51.029 --> 03:53.781
Better get going
or we'll be late for school.

04:04.192 --> 04:05.660
Bridgette, are you okay
with your spelling words?

04:05.728 --> 04:06.927
Yes, Mom.

04:06.995 --> 04:08.863
Hey, hey, hey,
don't forget your lunches.

04:08.931 --> 04:12.267
You got it? Here. Got it?
Give me a kiss. Bye. Bye.

04:12.334 --> 04:14.335
Come on, Megan.
I am!

05:49.932 --> 05:51.432
This isn't dirty.

06:23.364 --> 06:25.066
<i>Hey, girl, what's going on?</i>

06:25.133 --> 06:27.234
<i>I can't believe</i>
<i>it's Thursday already.</i>

06:27.302 --> 06:30.121
Tell me about it.
I have no idea where this week went.

06:30.189 --> 06:32.022
God, I wish you were here.

06:32.090 --> 06:35.293
I am having the hardest time trying
to pick out my dress for tonight.

06:35.360 --> 06:37.561
What about you guys?
You have any big plans for the weekend?

06:37.629 --> 06:39.980
What, besides jetting off
to Acapulco? No.

06:40.048 --> 06:43.150
Yeah, right.
Okay, I gotta go.

06:43.218 --> 06:45.720
I gotta figure out what I'm
doing with my life right now.

06:45.787 --> 06:47.755
<i>Oh, yeah?</i>
<i>What's his name?</i>

06:47.822 --> 06:50.675
His name? Well, the name
is really bad. It's Harry.

06:50.742 --> 06:52.977
<i>But, you never know,</i>
<i>he could be the one.</i>

06:53.045 --> 06:54.112
Bye.

06:58.350 --> 07:00.752
<i>You have one new message.</i>

07:00.819 --> 07:02.319
<i>First new message.</i>

07:02.387 --> 07:06.323
<i>Linda, listen, I need</i>
<i>to tell you something.</i>

07:08.193 --> 07:11.963
<i>I meant what I said in front of
the girls the other night, and...</i>

07:13.999 --> 07:15.099
<i>I just...</i>

07:17.118 --> 07:19.303
<i>I just want you to know that</i>

07:20.739 --> 07:23.307
<i>and to please remember it.</i>

07:23.375 --> 07:25.877
<i>Damn it.</i>
<i>Someone's calling. Hold on.</i>

07:26.979 --> 07:28.379
<i>Is that you?</i>

07:29.381 --> 07:30.915
<i>End of messages.</i>

07:34.953 --> 07:38.923
<i>If you leave a message, I'll get
back to you as soon as possible.</i>

07:38.990 --> 07:41.892
Hey, it's me.
I got your message.

07:41.960 --> 07:44.862
I don't know when you left it,

07:44.930 --> 07:47.464
but just call me
when you get mine.

07:47.532 --> 07:49.566
Okay? Bye.

08:17.145 --> 08:18.595
Mrs. Hanson?

08:18.663 --> 08:19.764
Yes?

08:19.831 --> 08:21.499
Linda Hanson?

08:22.000 --> 08:23.534
Uh-huh.

08:23.601 --> 08:26.304
I'm Sheriff Reilly.
Yes?

08:27.672 --> 08:30.190
I'm sorry to tell you this.

08:31.559 --> 08:34.227
Your husband, Jim...
Yeah?

08:34.296 --> 08:35.663
was in a car accident.

08:38.783 --> 08:40.517
He died on the scene.

08:51.529 --> 08:53.764
When?
Yesterday.

08:53.832 --> 08:57.668
No. No, it's impossible
because I just...

08:57.735 --> 09:01.172
I just heard his voice on the
answering machine, so...

09:02.975 --> 09:05.742
Well, I'm sorry, ma'am.

09:05.810 --> 09:08.879
We couldn't get to you
any sooner.

09:11.633 --> 09:15.269
The other driver
was in a truck. A semi.

09:15.337 --> 09:17.971
They're certain
it was instantaneous.

09:18.039 --> 09:19.740
It jackknifed. 220.

09:19.808 --> 09:23.110
He was on the highway,
around mile marker 220.

09:23.178 --> 09:25.813
The truck driver
was killed as well.

09:25.880 --> 09:28.583
I'm very sorry
about your husband.

09:28.650 --> 09:31.219
Ma'am is there anything
that I can do?

09:31.286 --> 09:36.107
Ma'am? Mrs. Hanson? Ma'am?

09:36.174 --> 09:38.859
Ma'am, is there anything
that I can do?

09:40.228 --> 09:42.612
Can I call someone for you?
Mmm-mmm.

09:49.070 --> 09:51.805
Let me leave you
my card. Okay?

09:51.873 --> 09:54.591
If you have any questions,
you just call me.

11:10.202 --> 11:11.969
What's wrong, Mommy?

11:18.393 --> 11:19.593
Mommy?

11:21.997 --> 11:23.631
What's wrong?

11:36.077 --> 11:38.128
It's about Daddy.

11:38.196 --> 11:40.430
Yeah?
Yeah.

11:43.634 --> 11:45.536
He's had a very bad accident.

11:46.854 --> 11:48.722
What kind of accident?

11:51.142 --> 11:53.110
When is he coming home?

11:55.513 --> 11:56.914
Is he okay?

11:59.617 --> 12:01.384
No, baby, he's not.

12:04.689 --> 12:06.023
Come here.

12:23.959 --> 12:26.927
Wow, I'm impressed.

12:26.995 --> 12:29.813
You guys got this far
all by yourself?

12:29.881 --> 12:31.632
Yeah.

12:31.700 --> 12:33.717
That's really amazing.

12:39.090 --> 12:39.710
<i>Hey, it's Annie.</i>

12:39.736 --> 12:40.857
<i>Leave a message at the beep,</i>

12:40.858 --> 12:43.093
<i>and I promise</i>
<i>I'll get right back to you.</i>

12:44.562 --> 12:46.330
Hey, Annie. It's me.

12:48.833 --> 12:51.902
Could you please call me as
soon as you get this message?

12:51.969 --> 12:53.303
Thank you.

12:56.341 --> 13:00.311
Wow, you girls
are doing so great.

13:01.679 --> 13:04.048
Daddy's better
at puzzles.

13:04.116 --> 13:06.083
He was going to help us.

13:30.976 --> 13:33.360
Hi, honey.
Hey.

13:34.395 --> 13:36.930
I think I finally
got them to sleep.

13:39.333 --> 13:40.701
Oh, I should say good night.

13:40.768 --> 13:43.303
No, don't do that.
They just fell asleep. Leave it.

13:43.371 --> 13:44.605
Okay.

13:46.440 --> 13:50.577
I was thinking about everything
we need to get done.

13:50.645 --> 13:56.316
Tomorrow we should probably start
looking into funeral arrangements.

13:56.384 --> 14:01.087
And then, you know, just see where
you are in terms of insurance.

14:01.155 --> 14:03.824
I'm not ready for that, Mom.

14:03.909 --> 14:07.043
Nobody's ready
for any of this, dear.

14:07.111 --> 14:10.464
But you'll be surprised
at how strong you're gonna be.

14:10.532 --> 14:12.682
You know when I lost your dad...
I can't stop thinking

14:12.751 --> 14:15.653
about our serving platter.

14:15.720 --> 14:19.239
What serving platter?
You know, the big one on the top shelf,

14:19.307 --> 14:21.641
the one that his folks gave us.

14:23.311 --> 14:25.545
I can't reach that.

14:25.613 --> 14:27.748
Jim... Jim does that
for me.

14:31.536 --> 14:35.773
Well, nobody expects you to get everything
done in the first few days, dear.

14:37.842 --> 14:39.909
I... I'm pretty tired.

14:39.977 --> 14:42.479
I'm gonna go lie down in the den.
Okay.

14:42.547 --> 14:46.500
I'll get some sheets
out of the closet.

14:46.568 --> 14:49.002
I'll be right up here
if you need me, dear.

17:06.641 --> 17:07.656
Mom?

17:10.611 --> 17:11.627
Mom?

18:28.956 --> 18:30.090
Jim?

18:36.364 --> 18:37.865
What's wrong?

18:44.789 --> 18:46.206
I don't... I don't know.

18:46.274 --> 18:48.475
I just had...
I just had the...

18:50.928 --> 18:53.096
I just had the strangest...

18:54.182 --> 18:55.999
What? What is it?

18:57.902 --> 19:01.037
Okay. I guess it's nothing.
It's nothing, it's nothing.

19:05.593 --> 19:08.879
Mom, we're late.
Three times and we get detention.

19:08.947 --> 19:10.513
And how is that a good
way to start the day?

19:10.582 --> 19:12.466
How about,
"Good morning, Mommy."

19:12.468 --> 19:14.050
Good morning.
"Good to see you, Mommy."

19:14.118 --> 19:15.535
Good morning.

19:15.603 --> 19:18.522
All right. I gotta get going.
Monday morning meeting.

19:20.358 --> 19:23.093
I got hugs for everybody.
All right, I gotta get going.

19:23.160 --> 19:26.230
I gotta train
this new assistant manager.

19:28.599 --> 19:31.751
I packed their lunches.
Ready to go.

19:31.819 --> 19:34.354
Are you okay
to take them to school?

19:35.956 --> 19:37.307
Mmm-hmm.

19:39.093 --> 19:41.561
Okay.

19:41.629 --> 19:44.130
You girls have fun at school now.
Bye-bye, Daddy.

19:44.198 --> 19:45.765
See you, honey.

20:04.001 --> 20:06.483
You okay with your
spelling words, Bridge?

20:06.509 --> 20:07.128
Yes.

20:07.171 --> 20:09.339
Hey, you guys,
don't forget your lunch.

20:12.927 --> 20:14.628
Come on, Megan,
get out of the car.

20:14.695 --> 20:15.879
I'm coming.

20:42.891 --> 20:45.392
<i>You have no messages.</i>

20:58.756 --> 20:59.873
Oh!

21:03.828 --> 21:05.395
Oh, shit.

21:14.104 --> 21:15.605
That was
quite a stop there.

21:15.673 --> 21:17.774
Yeah, I just...
I was totally...

21:19.660 --> 21:21.628
Yeah, I just, I got comp...

21:23.247 --> 21:24.414
Um...

21:24.481 --> 21:27.617
I just, I was totally
just distracted.

21:27.685 --> 21:30.086
Let's just take it
a little easy out there, huh?

21:30.154 --> 21:31.388
Sure.

21:31.455 --> 21:33.590
We don't want anyone
getting hurt now, do we?

21:35.910 --> 21:37.728
I'm trying to figure
out, should I call him?

21:37.795 --> 21:40.595
I mean, I really feel like I wanna
call him, but then it's kind of like

21:40.631 --> 21:41.998
I think that's
breaking the rules.

21:42.066 --> 21:44.535
I think it's better
if I just wait.

21:45.803 --> 21:47.154
What?

21:48.305 --> 21:50.540
Did we talk yesterday?

21:50.608 --> 21:51.958
Yeah. We talk every day.

21:52.026 --> 21:55.395
No, I mean, did I
leave you a message?

21:57.398 --> 22:00.266
I don't think so. Why?

22:00.334 --> 22:03.387
Wait a minute, hang on. I'm the one
with the crisis, okay? Are you...

22:03.389 --> 22:06.089
Are you sure you're all right?
Yeah.

22:06.156 --> 22:08.358
Everything's cool
with you and Jim?

22:10.044 --> 22:12.746
Yeah. Everything's
exactly the same.

23:23.835 --> 23:25.118
Oh, God.

24:12.884 --> 24:15.134
So, how was everybody's day?

24:17.872 --> 24:19.405
It was okay.

24:19.474 --> 24:21.575
Kind of boring.
Thank you.

24:21.642 --> 24:23.677
Yeah, kind of boring.

24:27.147 --> 24:29.332
Boring, huh?
Yeah.

25:43.707 --> 25:44.808
Jim?

26:09.083 --> 26:10.317
Jim.

26:10.968 --> 26:12.118
Jim.

26:19.209 --> 26:20.726
What the...

26:22.263 --> 26:23.446
Lithium?

26:26.133 --> 26:27.417
I...

26:44.318 --> 26:46.452
Thanks for coming.

26:46.520 --> 26:48.171
Here's your coffee.

26:49.356 --> 26:51.507
You never know.
Here she is.

26:51.575 --> 26:53.210
Hi, honey.

26:54.378 --> 26:55.845
Did you get
some rest?

26:55.913 --> 26:57.113
What's going on?

26:57.181 --> 26:58.731
Hey, how you feeling?

26:58.799 --> 27:00.733
Why don't you go upstairs
and let's get some clothes on.

27:00.801 --> 27:02.135
You wanna go upstairs
and get dressed?

27:02.202 --> 27:05.054
Where are the girls?
The girls are fine, dear.

27:05.122 --> 27:07.223
The girls are fine, honey.
Don't worry about the girls.

27:07.291 --> 27:08.575
This isn't right.

27:08.577 --> 27:10.060
What isn't, sweetie?
No, everything's fine.

27:10.127 --> 27:11.944
Do you need to go upstairs
and get more sleep? Or...

27:12.012 --> 27:14.664
No, no, no, I don't need
any more sleep,

27:14.732 --> 27:16.299
and I don't need
to wake up, either.

27:16.367 --> 27:17.967
Everything's
gonna be fine.

27:17.969 --> 27:20.436
No, Mother, everything is not fine!
Okay.

27:20.504 --> 27:23.856
Something is really, really wrong.
Okay.

27:23.924 --> 27:25.408
I'm...

27:26.610 --> 27:28.144
He's not dead.

27:40.124 --> 27:41.591
Hi, baby.

27:41.942 --> 27:43.293
Hey.

27:44.028 --> 27:45.611
Hi.

27:45.679 --> 27:48.214
Sorry I wasn't awake
when you guys got up.

27:48.281 --> 27:50.149
Grandma said we had to
let you sleep.

27:50.217 --> 27:52.885
No, baby. You can always
wake me up.

27:54.988 --> 27:56.839
What's your sister doing?

27:56.907 --> 27:59.141
Swinging.
Yeah?

27:59.209 --> 28:02.144
I think she's sad.
Yeah.

28:02.212 --> 28:04.430
We're all a little sad
right now.

28:13.273 --> 28:14.357
Hi, baby.

28:24.501 --> 28:25.951
Oh, my God.

28:26.620 --> 28:28.371
Oh, my God, baby.

28:28.439 --> 28:31.056
Baby, what happened
to your face?

28:31.942 --> 28:33.243
Baby, talk to me.

28:33.310 --> 28:35.245
How did you get these cuts?
Who did this to you, baby?

28:35.312 --> 28:37.697
Did what?
The cuts! The cuts on your face.

28:37.765 --> 28:39.065
There's no cuts, Mommy.

28:39.132 --> 28:41.117
What are you talking about?

28:41.185 --> 28:45.054
She's perfect,
like a beautiful princess.

28:51.411 --> 28:54.447
Oh, God, come here. Come here.
Just hold onto me.

28:54.514 --> 28:57.784
It's gonna be okay.
It's gonna be okay. Come here.

28:57.851 --> 28:59.986
It's gonna be all right.
Everything's gonna be all right.

29:00.054 --> 29:02.021
Everything's gonna be
all right.

29:02.089 --> 29:04.190
Mommy?
Yeah?

29:04.341 --> 29:06.876
What was it like
when Daddy died?

29:08.362 --> 29:11.431
I don't know, baby.
I wasn't there.

29:11.498 --> 29:14.116
So how did you know
he died then?

29:48.819 --> 29:50.369
Are you all right?

29:51.621 --> 29:54.206
What if this is a mistake?

29:54.358 --> 29:56.159
What do you mean, "a mistake"?

29:56.227 --> 29:58.661
People just don't die one day and
are okay the next day, that's all.

29:58.729 --> 30:00.563
It's not a mistake. Jim's...

30:00.630 --> 30:02.415
Okay, Mom, did you see
inside the casket?

30:02.483 --> 30:04.316
No, I didn't see, dear,
but it doesn't...

30:04.384 --> 30:06.302
Okay, well something is seriously
fucked up with this situation.

30:06.369 --> 30:08.489
Linda? We need to go in the church now.
Come on, dear.

30:08.538 --> 30:10.473
No, you need
to take the kids inside.

30:10.541 --> 30:12.442
Well, why don't you come inside with us?
Just take the kids inside.

30:12.510 --> 30:14.810
Go ahead, go ahead
with the kids. Linda.

30:14.812 --> 30:15.828
Linda?

30:21.018 --> 30:22.519
Here she is.

30:24.755 --> 30:26.389
Hello, Mrs. Hanson.

30:26.540 --> 30:28.808
I just want you to know
that everything's on schedule.

30:28.876 --> 30:30.316
I need for you
to open up the casket.

30:30.327 --> 30:33.095
No, no, I don't think that
would be a very good idea.

30:33.163 --> 30:34.897
Open up the casket,
God damn it.

30:34.965 --> 30:36.482
Open it up! Open it up!

30:36.550 --> 30:38.468
Open it! Open it! Open it!
Mrs. Hanson!

30:38.535 --> 30:40.553
What?
I beg you to let this go.

30:40.621 --> 30:42.872
Don't do this to me.
Mrs. Hanson, I have to warn you.

30:42.874 --> 30:44.874
There was a problem with the body.
What kind of problem?

30:45.025 --> 30:47.760
They didn't want to tell you the way
he died. They didn't want to tell you.

30:47.828 --> 30:48.878
What about
the way that he died?

30:48.945 --> 30:50.413
There was a deep cut,
a severing.

30:50.481 --> 30:52.915
What kind of severing?
Well, it...

30:52.983 --> 30:55.234
Oh, my God.
No! No!

30:57.871 --> 31:01.357
Get out of the way!
Stop it! Let go of me!

31:01.425 --> 31:04.076
Let go! Let go of me!

31:04.144 --> 31:05.561
No!

31:05.629 --> 31:06.896
No!

31:07.430 --> 31:08.831
No!

31:17.324 --> 31:20.110
Jim left this world
a beloved person.

31:22.012 --> 31:24.947
His friends spoke
about his kindness,

31:25.015 --> 31:26.382
his laugh,

31:27.251 --> 31:29.785
his graciousness,

31:29.853 --> 31:34.157
his helpfulness and consideration
to everyone around him.

31:36.627 --> 31:40.263
But his greatest devotion
was to his family.

31:41.865 --> 31:44.483
His "girls" as he liked
to refer to them.

31:45.152 --> 31:47.854
His lovely wife, Linda.

31:47.921 --> 31:50.406
His precious daughters,
Megan and Bridgette.

31:50.474 --> 31:51.808
Mom?

31:51.876 --> 31:53.843
What?

31:53.911 --> 31:54.440
Who is that?

31:54.466 --> 31:56.538
And what better tribute
is there to any man.

31:56.580 --> 31:58.080
Who?
Her, that woman.

31:58.148 --> 32:01.317
Than the reflection
of his own love in the hearts

32:01.385 --> 32:04.120
of the loved ones he left behind.
I don't know, dear.

32:05.355 --> 32:08.207
And so, dear friends...
Linda?

32:08.275 --> 32:10.876
It's okay. It's okay.
...let us pray.

32:15.499 --> 32:20.603
"Our Father, who art in
heaven, hallowed be Thy name.

32:20.671 --> 32:25.974
"Thy kingdom come, Thy will be
done on earth as it is in heaven."

32:30.481 --> 32:33.499
Wait. No, please,
wait. Wait.

32:34.851 --> 32:36.869
